// 4.5 Describe the four basic elements of counter-controlled repetition.
// Answer:
// Counter-controlled repetition requires four basic elements:
//
// 1. Control Variable (Loop Counter):
//    A variable used to count the number of times the loop executes.
//
// 2. Initial Value:
//    The starting value assigned to the control variable before the loop begins.
//
// 3. Increment (or Decrement):
//    The change applied to the control variable after each iteration.
//
// 4. Loop-Continuation Condition:
//    The condition that determines whether the loop should continue running or stop.
